KPS 
              SPECIAL SITUATIONS FUND, L.P. CREATES CURTIS PAPERS, INC.: 
              COMPLETES ACQUISITION OF SPECIALTY AND FINE PAPERS BUSINESSES FROM 
              CROWN VANTAGE



New 
              York, NY (March 2, 2001) --  
              KPS Special Situations Fund, L.P. ("KPS") announced 
              the purchase of certain assets of Crown Vantage Inc. and the
              formation of Curtis Papers, Inc. Curtis Papers was formed to own 
              and
              operate the specialty paper and premium papers businesses of Crown 
              Vantage.
              KPS invested $10 million of equity to fund the transaction. 
The specialty papers business of Curtis Papers 
              will be conducted under the
              name of Curtis Specialty Papers and will include the paper mills 
              in Port
              Huron, Michigan and Milford, New Jersey. Curtis Specialty Papers 
              is a
              leading manufacturer of premium uncoated and coated papers for a 
              wide range
              of end use markets including food service, flexible packaging, label 
              and
              release and custom converting. Products are marketed under such 
              well-known
              names as Staynles ® and Conquest ®. 
The premium papers business will operate under 
              the name of Curtis Fine
              Papers and will conduct operations out of a paper mill in Adams,
              Massachusetts and a coating and converting facility in Richmond, 
              Virginia.
              Curtis Fine Papers is one of the oldest and best know manufacturers 
              of text
              and cover and premium printing grades and markets its products under 
              trade
              names such as Curtis Brightwater®, Linen®, Flannel® 
              and King James®. Curtis
              Fine Papers is also a leading producer of custom technical specialties 
              for a
              wide range of demanding end uses. Crown Vantage will continue to 
              run the
              text and cover mill in Ypsilanti, Michigan under an operating agreement 
              with
              Curtis Papers for up to six months while the grades produced in 
              Ypsilanti
              are transitioned to the Adams Mill. 
In addition to the four domestic facilities, the 
              new company will also own
              the stock of Curtis Papers, Ltd., which consists of two premium 
              paper mills
              in Scotland. The Scottish mills market premium papers under the 
              name of
              Curtis Classic in the U.K. and throughout Europe.
Curtis Papers will have capacity to produce 200,000 annual tons 
              of paper
              products and will generate revenues in excess of $250 million. The 
              new
              company will employ over 850 domestically and in the U.K. 

              "The new Curtis Papers has a very loyal customer base, a broad 
              family of
              high quality and unique products, and a talented group of employees. 
              We
              look forward to building on this foundation and creating a vibrant 
              and
              successful specialty paper company through a combination of cost 
              reduction,
              focused capital investment and new product introductions", 
              said David
              Shapiro, a managing principal of KPS. Curtis Papers, Inc. will be 
              led by an
              experienced management team, including two new additions: President 
              and
              Chief Executive Officer, Bruce Curley, formerly with the Mead Corporation
              and Chief Financial Officer, Keith McKinnish, formerly with Champion
              International. Charles Whitaker, is joining the new company from 
              Crown
              Vantage as President of Curtis Fine Papers. Allan Milne will retain 
              his
              current position as Managing Director of Curtis Fine Paper, Ltd.
This transaction is KPS's third investment in the 
              forest products industry:
              KPS created Blue Ridge Paper Products, Inc. in May of 1999 and Blue 
              Heron
              Paper Company in May of 2000. KPS was introduced to the Crown Vantage
              opportunity by representatives of the Paper, Allied-Industrial, 
              Chemical and
              Energy Workers International Union ("PACE"). 
KPS 
              Special Situations Fund, L.P., founded and managed by Eugene Keilin, 
              David Shapiro and Michael Psaros, is a New York City-based private 
              equity fund focused on constructive investing in restructurings, 
              turnarounds and other special situations. More information on KPS 
              and its portfolio companies and investment strategy can be found 
              at www.kpsfund.com .




 














